::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 128 m.ogg}} {{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 128 f.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' (Trailblazer), you did the right thing. I'm afraid this is how the Plagues Author operates &mdash; using notions of power and life to draw countless people like Zhixin away from bright futures... down a path of no return.
::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 129.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' You've managed to shine a light on the darkness of the enemy. With this intelligence, the Seat of Divine Foresight will be able to improve its strategy...
::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 130.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' ...and for all your efforts, please accept this reward.
::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 131.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' Is there anything else you'd like to know about?
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Tell me about the current state of the Disciples of Sanctus Medicus...
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 132.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' The current state... I'm afraid we know next to nothing. We dispatched agents, but they were only able to linger on the edges of the organization. Your operation is the furthest anyone's managed to infiltrate.
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 133.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' The Seat of Divine Foresight is still striving to answer one question: Is this but the resurgent shadow of an organization silenced a thousand years ago... or have they been lurking in the darkness all along?
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 134.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' Whatever the case, this sudden re-emergence hints at a hidden conspiracy...
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 135.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' It's troubled me deeply over recent few months... it's hard to tell what all of this is building towards.
::;(Return to previous option selection)
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Did you send a lot of people undercover?
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 136.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' Not at all. The Disciples' secret letter makes it sound as if we infiltrated their ranks in great numbers... The reality is that only a handful of agents have successfully slipped into the organization...
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 137.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' ...and the majority of them lacked the strength you had to make it back unscathed after their identity was exposed. They didn't have the wisdom and good fortune to gain the organization's trust quickly...
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 138.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' An agent can't actually consume those pellets of the Disciples... doing so would mean the end of their life as they knew it.
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 139.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' The point is, there hasn't been anyone like you who managed to delve into the group's core and obtain so much firsthand information.
::;(Return to previous option selection)
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Tell me about the beliefs of the Disciples of Sanctus Medicus...
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 140.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' Thousand-Handed Merciful Medicus' Salvation is a manuscript transcribed from a sacred text &mdash; I don't know where the Disciples obtained it. It likely consists of fragments of banned works from the {{Rubi|befall era|Theophany Era}}.
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 141.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' As I see it, there isn't anything particularly alarming about the text. It recalls the acts of the Plagues Author's warped creatures from an equally warped perspective...
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 142.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' The scripture doesn't have the power to lead people astray &mdash; they do that to themselves... but it does feed lies and false hope.
::;(Return to previous option selection)
::{{DIcon|Exit}} About the prescription that Zhixin gave me...
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 143.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' The prescription you acquired is... beyond my knowledge.
:::{{A|VO side2 ywmc1 qingzu 144.ogg}} '''Qingzu:''' There are a few reliable alchemists that reside in Exalting Sanctum. I'd like to ask you to consult with them on the particulars of the prescription. This will allow the Seat of Divine Foresight to have a clear target for creating an antidote...
